<br />
If true, it is kind of a bummer.  The guy is abrasive, but it was useful having a high profile person screaming about some of the problems with the game after Lum moved from ranter to Mythic employee, and providing a high-traffic board where people were free to criticize the game after Whineplay exploded.  I guess we'll have to find a new ranter for Warcraft to scream about its problems.<br />
<br />
Of course, this will have me taking everything he said so far about WoW with a metric ton of salt, instead of the mere pound of salt I used before.<br />
<br />
Flames ahoy!</p>
	
	
	
