	<p>Hell I don't care if he's is a foulmouthed, spoiled little brat, I always assumed that was just an alter ego. As long as the quests are good, I don't care what type of person is writing them.<br />
<br />
I do care that his opinion for the last 4 years was casual gamers can go screw themselves. The only valid game is the end game and huge raids and no one else matters. This person in charge of quest has my hopes sinking. I had hoped to escape EQ's raid or die mentality. Now not only was Furor one of their premeire beta boys, now he's actually payed and in charge of content. Not itemization either, he's in charge of quests, the one feature of this game that I was looking forward to.<br />
<br />
The above poster put it well, I don't hate furor but he does represent everything I dislike about the direction of EQ(IMHO). Now he's payed to create content. I can't help but worry about the future of WoW or who its going to be designed for.<br />
<br />
Is my first newbie quest going to require I mobilized 74 people at once to deliver our guild notes simulataneously across town. The more people I can get to join me, the more uber my starting tunic will be? Why not start the game off right and show those casual losers from level one who's the uberest!</p>
	
	
	
	
	
