	<td class="alt2" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>I share the disgust with Furor expressed by others.  Yes, I wish he was working on a game that I figured I'd never play instead of one that I'm excited about.  That said, Blizz has already designed a lot of content. They don't seem inclined to make WoW powergamer/uber-guild centric, and I don't expect them to hand Furor the keys to the car and say, "It's all yours now, do what you want with it."   Even then, I can't say I know for sure how he would develop WoW.  Furor may be a jerk, but I'm not going to shy away from the game because of the personality of a developer as long as that personality isn't effecting my gameplay (i.e. a bug report is met with a response of "FU!").  Who knows what aholes roamed the halls of Verant/SOE during whatever period you were really enjoying EQ.  This news alone should not make anyone say, "No WoW for me."  If it's a good game, the fact that Furor is back there somewhere working on some portion of content will be the last thing on your mind.</p>
	
	
	
	
	
