	<p>I can go both ways on this one.  On the one hand I'm not sure Furor knows enough about the "casual style" I play to make constructive comments.  On the other hand, he (apparently) lives and breaths MMORG's, so having someone like that working on a game should bring a lot of valuable insights to the development team.<br />
<br />
As to his presentation style...I'm willing to bet that in face to face situations he tones down a bit  <img src="images/smilies/tongue.gif" border="0" alt="" title="stick out tongue" smilieid="6" /> .  Also, I think it's good to have a level of contention - as long as people can vehemently debate without taking things personally this approach oftentimes results in a more thorough discussion and a better solution in the end.  (mainly because people are actually saying what they feel as opposed to tempering their comments to avoid possibly offending someone)</p>
	
	
	
